I am currently the Director of Engineering at the NYC Digital Service, within the NYC Office of Technology and Innovation.

Previously, I was an Engineering Manager at the Democratic National Committee Tech Team, a faculty member at the University of Michigan School of Information, and the Co-Director of the Summer Guild pre-college computing program in 2018.

I'm a software engineer and I am a teacher within everything I do. I like to have a role in building tech that makes people's lives easier, better, and/or more fun. I enjoy being part of teams who learn from each other, try new things, and ship -- both in teams and in the classroom.

I've worked in research labs, startups, and in civic technology. I've taught all levels of computer programming and related topics to college students used to research computing education, which informs all of my work.

I used to use Twitter, but not lately; you can find me on Mastodon at jczetta@med-mastodon occasionally. My personal GitHub is separate from my work GitHub so it's pretty sparse these days -- when I'm not working, I'm often bookbinding, working with film (photography), biking, or something involving food.

You can find more about me at the surrounding links, or reach out: jczetta at gmail.
